{"parse":{"title":"AN/MRN-1","pageid":24587695,"revid":846301816,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>AN/MRN-1</b> was an instrument approach <a href=\"/wiki/Localizer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Localizer\">localizer</a> used by the <a href=\"/wiki/Army_Air_Force\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Army Air Force\">Army Air Force</a> during and after <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a>. It was standardized on 3 July 1942. It replaced the SCR-241, and was a component of SCS-51.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Use\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Use</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Components\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Components</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aircraft_components\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aircraft components</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Use\">Use</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=AN/MRN-1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Use\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The transmitter provides a signal to guide the <b>RC-103</b> equipped aircraft to the centerline of a runway. The set radiates two intersecting field patterns, one of which is modulated at an audio frequency of 90 cycles per second, and the other at an audio frequency of 150 cycles per second. the shape of the radiated patterns is such that they intersect in a vertical plane called the \"course\", which can be oriented (by positioning the truck) to intersect the ground in a line which coincides with the centerline of a landing runway. The range of the equipment is a function of the elevation of the receiving antenna: approximately 40 miles at an elevation of 2,500 feet, 70 miles at 6,000 feet, and 100 miles at 10,000 feet. The transmitter, <b>BC-751-A</b> has a frequency range from 108.3 to 110.3 Mc. power output is 25 Watts.\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>AN/CRN-3</b> is the same equipment except without the K-53 truck, thereby making it air transportable, components are housed in a tent.</li></ul>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:ILS_localizer_illustration.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/05/ILS_localizer_illustration.svg/300px-ILS_localizer_illustration.svg.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"310\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/05/ILS_localizer_illustration.svg/450px-ILS_localizer_illustration.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/05/ILS_localizer_illustration.svg/600px-ILS_localizer_illustration.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"580\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:ILS_localizer_illustration.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The emission patterns of the localizer and glideslope signals. Note that the glideslope beams are partly formed by the reflection of the glideslope aerial in the ground plane.</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Components\">Components</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=AN/MRN-1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Components\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The AN/MRN-1 is mounted in a <a href=\"/wiki/K-53_truck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"K-53 truck\">K-53 truck</a> and is made up of the following components.\n</p>\n<ul><li>BC-915 control box</li>\n<li>BC-751 radio transmitter</li>\n<li>BC-752 <a href=\"/wiki/Modulator\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Modulator\">Modulator</a> and bridge</li>\n<li>BC-753 course detector fixed</li>\n<li>BC-754 course detector portable</li>\n<li>BC-755 field intensity meter</li>\n<li>BC-777 indicator (alarm)</li>\n<li>RC-109 antenna (5 <a href=\"/wiki/Alford_loops\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alford loops\">alford loops</a> in a horizontal plane)</li>\n<li>An <a href=\"/wiki/SCR-610\" title=\"SCR-610\">SCR-610</a> is provided for ground communications</li>\n<li>power is provided by a PE-141 <a href=\"/wiki/Electrical_generator\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Electrical generator\">generator</a> (115 volts)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aircraft_components\">Aircraft components</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=AN/MRN-1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Aircraft components\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <b>RC-103-A</b> is an airborne localizer receiver used to indicate a landing course in conjunction with the AAF instrument approach system. signals received from a transmitter, located at one end of the runway to be used, are fed into the cross-pointer indicator to indicate \"on course\", \"fly right\" or \"fly left\". Audio indication is also provided.\n</p>\n<dl><dd>Antenna system AS-27/ARN-5 is used with the dual installation of the localizer and glide path receivers. Antenna AN-100 is used when only the localizer receiver is installed in the aircraft.</dd></dl>\n<ul><li>RC-103 components include</li>\n<li>Indicator I-101-C</li>\n<li>BC-732 control box</li>\n<li>BC-733 Receiver W/ DM-53 <a href=\"/wiki/Dynamotor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dynamotor\">Dynamotor</a></li>\n<li>AN-100 Antenna (localizer only)</li>\n<li>AS-27/ARN-5 Antenna system (combination)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=AN/MRN-1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px\">\n<ul style=\"display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold\">\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><img alt=\"seal\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/28px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/42px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/56px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"356\" data-file-hei